        "Topic Identification and Description": "nth term of an AP: This topic involves identifying the first term ($a$), the common difference ($d$), and the term number ($n$) to calculate the specific value of the $n^{\\text{th}}$ term ($a_n$) of a sequence defined by a constant difference between consecutive terms.",
